div.p:
In the third exhortation to praise God, expressely directed to Ierusalem and Sion, representing the Church in all ages; 

                     •
                  earn, 1. Albeit all the earth be obliged to praise God, yet only the Lords people are the right estimators of his glory, and the fit proclaimers of his praise: Praise the Lord, O Ierusalem. 2. Albeit all the creatures are the Lords, yet the Church is the Lords in a more nigh relation; for the Church may claim interest in God as her own by Covenant; Praise thy God, O Zion.
